                  <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Yes. While many prop firms banned American traders due to regulatory pressures, FXIFY legally accepts US traders by utilizing US-compliant tech platforms like DXtrade.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-slate-950 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800">
                  <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-2">Can I use MetaTrader 4 or 5 as a US resident?</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">No. Due to MetaQuotes' restrictions on US IP addresses for offshore firms, FXIFY provides US residents with DXtrade. The platform features native TradingView charting integrations, making the transition seamless.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-slate-950 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800">
                  <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-2">Are there consistency rules on FXIFY?</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">On FXIFY's standard evaluation accounts (1-Phase, 2-Phase, and 3-Phase), there are no consistency rules. You can trade at your own pace with unlimited trading days. (Note: Instant Funding Lite does feature consistency rules to balance the immediate risk).</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-slate-950 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800">
                  <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-2">How do I withdraw my profits in the US?</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">US traders can seamlessly withdraw their profit splits using cryptocurrency (USDT/USDC/BTC) for maximum speed, bypassing traditional banking delays.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section id="verdict" class="scroll-mt-32">
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-white mb-8 border-l-4 border-blue-600 pl-6">Final Verdict: Claim Your {currentYear} Discount</h2>
